      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 915: The retry counter is conversation-wide, but validation failures can be caused by one bad or malicious device serving an invalid clone while another member/device may still have a valid repository. After three failures from the same bad source, this permanently suppresses future clone attempts from all devices for this in-memory conversation, which can make a recoverable invitation unrecoverable. Track validation failures per source device/peer, or only mark unrecoverable after exhausting distinct clone sources. For example:\n```suggestion\nstd::map\u003cstd::string, unsigned\u003e validationFailuresByDevice {};\n\nbool isUnrecoverable(const std::string\u0026 deviceId) const\n{\n    auto it \u003d validationFailuresByDevice.find(deviceId);\n    return it !\u003d validationFailuresByDevice.end() \u0026\u0026 it-\u003esecond \u003e\u003d MAX_VALIDATION_FAILURES;\n}\n```",
