      "message": "[Critical] Line 2895: Throwing `InvalidRepositoryError` changes the error contract of `cloneConversation()` from returning an empty result to throwing, but this patch only documents one caller. Any existing or future caller that expects the documented pair-return behavior can now terminate the operation if the exception escapes. Either keep the return-value contract and surface the reason explicitly, or ensure every caller catches `InvalidRepositoryError`. A safer API would encode the failure mode in the return type instead of relying on an unchecked exception.",
